  "text": "The main feature of the Sparre Andersen model, which fundamentally differentiate this paper with all existing works is that the process Q is non-Markovian in general (unless the counting process N is a Poisson process), consequently we can not directly apply the dynamic programming approach. We shall therefore first apply the so-called Backward Markovization technique (cf. e.g., [CITATION_1] ) to overcome this obstacle. More precisely, we define a new process",
